   <text>
      <body>
         <div>

            <p>
                    <seg corresp="#KR2p0038_tls_001-1a.1" xml:lang="en">I have heard it said: </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0038_tls_001-1a.2" xml:lang="en">“As for the way in which formerly the enlightened kings of the three dynasties possessed all under Heaven, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0038_tls_001-1a.3" xml:lang="en">nobody gave it (to them), </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0038_tls_001-1a.4" xml:lang="en">but they obtained it (=all under Heaven) entirely (?) (by themselves). </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0038_tls_001-1a.5" xml:lang="en">The people all thought (it) to be righteous, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0038_tls_001-1a.6" xml:lang="en">and therefore (the kings) protected them with trust, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0038_tls_001-1a.7" xml:lang="en">educated them with righteousness, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0038_tls_001-1a.8" xml:lang="en">enacted it with ritual propriety. </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0038_tls_001-1a.9" xml:lang="en">In chaotic times, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0038_tls_001-1a.10" xml:lang="en">the kings would give the state and clan and the lands to others, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0038_tls_001-1a.11" xml:lang="en">and the people would not in any case find it righteous. </seg>
                </p>

            <p>
                    <seg corresp="#KR2p0038_tls_001-2a.1" xml:lang="en">[...] rites, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0038_tls_001-2a.2" xml:lang="en">then (they will be) scarce in humanity (?), </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0038_tls_001-2a.3" xml:lang="en">if one teaches them by means of punishments </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0038_tls_001-2a.4" xml:lang="en">then they will be driven out [of the country]. </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0038_tls_001-2a.5" xml:lang="en">I have heard it said: </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0038_tls_001-2a.6" xml:lang="en">“As good people treat people well (?), </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0038_tls_001-2a.7" xml:lang="en">therefore they obtain unique persons among the worthy and the shi officials, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0038_tls_001-2a.8" xml:lang="en">unique persons are praised [...] </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0038_tls_001-2a.9" xml:lang="en">four neighbors. </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0038_tls_001-2a.10" xml:lang="en">If one loses unique persons among the worthy and the shi officials, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0038_tls_001-2a.11" xml:lang="en">(then) slander also follows this, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0038_tls_001-2a.12" xml:lang="en">therefore the gentleman should be cautious in his words </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0038_tls_001-2a.13" xml:lang="en">but not be (too) cautious in his acts [...] </seg>
                </p>

            <p>
                    <seg corresp="#KR2p0038_tls_001-3a.1" xml:lang="en">You should not be violent, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0038_tls_001-3a.2" xml:lang="en">you should not be tyrannical, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0038_tls_001-3a.3" xml:lang="en">you should not be ravenous, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0038_tls_001-3a.4" xml:lang="en">you should not be covetous. </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0038_tls_001-3a.5" xml:lang="en">Not being cultivated and not being martial, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0038_tls_001-3a.6" xml:lang="en">(but still) asking them (=the people) necessarily to be accomplished, (when proposing something making sure to live up to it CH) </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0038_tls_001-3a.7" xml:lang="en">then one is violent; </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0038_tls_001-3a.8" xml:lang="en">not to teach but to kill, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0038_tls_001-3a.9" xml:lang="en">then one is tyrannical; </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0038_tls_001-3a.10" xml:lang="en">to give orders without timeliness, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0038_tls_001-3a.11" xml:lang="en">(but still expecting) that affairs will necessarily have a deadline, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0038_tls_001-3a.12" xml:lang="en">then one is ravenous; </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0038_tls_001-3a.13" xml:lang="en">to pervert affairs for the sake of profit, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0038_tls_001-3a.14" xml:lang="en">then one is covetous. </seg>
                </p>

            <p>
                    <seg corresp="#KR2p0038_tls_001-4a.1" xml:lang="en">I have heard it said: </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0038_tls_001-4a.2" xml:lang="en">“Conducting the government, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0038_tls_001-4a.3" xml:lang="en">(one should) use the five virtues, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0038_tls_001-4a.4" xml:lang="en">strengthen the three laws, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0038_tls_001-4a.5" xml:lang="en">remove the ten resentments. </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0038_tls_001-4a.6" xml:lang="en">The five virtues: </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0038_tls_001-4a.7" xml:lang="en">the first is called magnanimity, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0038_tls_001-4a.8" xml:lang="en">the second is called reverence, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0038_tls_001-4a.9" xml:lang="en">the third is called benevolence, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0038_tls_001-4a.10" xml:lang="en">the fourth is called humanity, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0038_tls_001-4a.11" xml:lang="en">the fifth is called respect. </seg>
                </p>

            <p>
                    <seg corresp="#KR2p0038_tls_001-5a.1" xml:lang="en">If the gentleman is not magnanimous </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0038_tls_001-5a.2" xml:lang="en">then there is nothing by which means to support the hundred surnames; </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0038_tls_001-5a.3" xml:lang="en">if he is not reverent, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0038_tls_001-5a.4" xml:lang="en">then there is nothing by which means to remove shame, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0038_tls_001-5a.5" xml:lang="en">if he is not benevolent, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0038_tls_001-5a.6" xml:lang="en">then there is nothing by which means to gather the people, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0038_tls_001-5a.7" xml:lang="en">if he is not humane </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0038_tls_001-5a.8" xml:lang="en">then there is nothing by which means to enact governance, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0038_tls_001-5a.9" xml:lang="en">if he is not respectful </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0038_tls_001-5a.10" xml:lang="en">then affairs will not have completion. </seg>
                </p>

            <p>
                    <seg corresp="#KR2p0038_tls_001-6a.1" xml:lang="en">The three laws: </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0038_tls_001-6a.2" xml:lang="en">to hold to rank (?), </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0038_tls_001-6a.3" xml:lang="en">to look above (?), </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0038_tls_001-6a.4" xml:lang="en">to finish eating (?) [...] </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0038_tls_001-6a.5" xml:lang="en">(The ninth resentment) says </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0038_tls_001-6a.6" xml:lang="en">to interfere with other people’s tasks, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0038_tls_001-6a.7" xml:lang="en">the tenth says </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0038_tls_001-6a.8" xml:lang="en">to be benevolent in words </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0038_tls_001-6a.9" xml:lang="en">and not follow (promises with actions). </seg>
                </p>

            <p>
                    <seg corresp="#KR2p0038_tls_001-7a.1" xml:lang="en">As for making state and clans prosper </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0038_tls_001-7a.2" xml:lang="en">and for regulating government and education, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0038_tls_001-7a.3" xml:lang="en">if one follows orders, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0038_tls_001-7a.4" xml:lang="en">then governors will not toil (in vain); </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0038_tls_001-7a.5" xml:lang="en">embracing restraint and anticipating (=preventing) evil, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0038_tls_001-7a.6" xml:lang="en">then it starts from oneself. </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0038_tls_001-7a.7" xml:lang="en">making excellence manifest and encouraging trust, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0038_tls_001-7a.8" xml:lang="en">then hypocrisy will not display itself. </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0038_tls_001-7a.9" xml:lang="en">not encroaching on people’s collected items (property), </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0038_tls_001-7a.10" xml:lang="en">then they will unify </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0038_tls_001-7a.11" xml:lang="en">Not promulgating laws to spread (one’s) wickedness, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0038_tls_001-7a.12" xml:lang="en">then the people will not complain. </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0038_tls_001-7a.13" xml:lang="en">I have heard it said: [...] </seg>
                </p>

            <p>
                    <seg corresp="#KR2p0038_tls_001-8a.1" xml:lang="en">[...] and not wise, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0038_tls_001-8a.2" xml:lang="en">then one will meet disaster and harm. </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0038_tls_001-8a.3" xml:lang="en">I have heard it said: </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0038_tls_001-8a.4" xml:lang="en">“In conducting the government there are seven (dangerous) occasions, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0038_tls_001-8a.5" xml:lang="en">if one is (too) hard then they will feel oppressed, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0038_tls_001-8a.6" xml:lang="en">if one is (too) authoritarian then the people will not be (easily) led, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0038_tls_001-8a.7" xml:lang="en">if one is (too) harsh then one will lose the masses, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0038_tls_001-8a.8" xml:lang="en">if one is dissolute then he will have no intimates, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0038_tls_001-8a.9" xml:lang="en">if one uses fines (too harshly) then the people will escape, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0038_tls_001-8a.10" xml:lang="en">if one loves punishments [...] </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0038_tls_001-8a.11" xml:lang="en">then the people will create chaos. </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0038_tls_001-8a.12" xml:lang="en">In all cases these seven </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0038_tls_001-8a.13" xml:lang="en">are what endangers the government. </seg>
                </p>

            <p>
                    <seg corresp="#KR2p0038_tls_001-9a.1" xml:lang="en">I have heard it said: </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0038_tls_001-9a.2" xml:lang="en">“If pneuma and intent are not in accord, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0038_tls_001-9a.3" xml:lang="en">.......their affairs do not [...] </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0038_tls_001-9a.4" xml:lang="en">[I have heard it] said: </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0038_tls_001-9a.5" xml:lang="en">“The things the governor need to occupy themselves with, are three: </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0038_tls_001-9a.6" xml:lang="en">respect, well chosen words (?) and trust. </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0038_tls_001-9a.7" xml:lang="en">If one is trusted then one will obtain the masses, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0038_tls_001-9a.8" xml:lang="en">if one chooses words well then he can avert mistakes, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0038_tls_001-9a.9" xml:lang="en">by averting mistakes thereby [...] </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0038_tls_001-9a.10" xml:lang="en">Only after that one can establish the way. </seg>
                </p>

            <p>
                    <seg corresp="#KR2p0038_tls_001-10a.1" xml:lang="en">I have heard it said: </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0038_tls_001-10a.2" xml:lang="en">“As for the gentleman’s reciprocal approaching [=his social interactions], </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0038_tls_001-10a.3" xml:lang="en">he should not necessarily find pleasure in being close to his intimates [...] </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0038_tls_001-10a.4" xml:lang="en">having something in surplus </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0038_tls_001-10a.5" xml:lang="en">and not daring to bring it to the extreme, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0038_tls_001-10a.6" xml:lang="en">having less than enough of something </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0038_tls_001-10a.7" xml:lang="en">and not daring not to [...] </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0038_tls_001-10a.8" xml:lang="en">[...] continuing offense with offense (?), </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0038_tls_001-10a.9" xml:lang="en">seeing unsuitable behavior </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0038_tls_001-10a.10" xml:lang="en">and thereby causing it to get out (?) </seg>
                </p>

            <p>
                    <seg corresp="#KR2p0038_tls_001-11a.1" xml:lang="en">I have heard it said: </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0038_tls_001-11a.2" xml:lang="en">“When the gentleman is happy then he sets the government into order, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0038_tls_001-11a.3" xml:lang="en">when he is grieved then [...] he reverts (to himself), </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0038_tls_001-11a.4" xml:lang="en">when the petty person is happy then he is dubious, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0038_tls_001-11a.5" xml:lang="en">when he is grieved then he is confused, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0038_tls_001-11a.6" xml:lang="en">when he is angered then he wants to prevaricate, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0038_tls_001-11a.7" xml:lang="en">when he is scared then he rebels, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0038_tls_001-11a.8" xml:lang="en">when he is shamed then he offends. </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0038_tls_001-11a.9" xml:lang="en">I have heard it said: </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0038_tls_001-11a.10" xml:lang="en">“The conduct of government, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0038_tls_001-11a.11" xml:lang="en">if it is not well ordered then it is in chaos, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0038_tls_001-11a.12" xml:lang="en">if order is achieved then [...] </seg>
                </p>

            <p>
                    <seg corresp="#KR2p0038_tls_001-12a.1" xml:lang="en">[When the gentleman precedes] others </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0038_tls_001-12a.2" xml:lang="en">then he opens the road for them, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0038_tls_001-12a.3" xml:lang="en">when he is behind others </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0038_tls_001-12a.4" xml:lang="en">then he serves them and helps them, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0038_tls_001-12a.5" xml:lang="en">therefore it is said that </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0038_tls_001-12a.6" xml:lang="en">the gentleman is difficult to obtain </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0038_tls_001-12a.7" xml:lang="en">but easy to employ, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0038_tls_001-12a.8" xml:lang="en">in his deployment of the people </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0038_tls_001-12a.9" xml:lang="en">he treats them as (skilfully as a craftsman treats his) tools. </seg>
                </p>

            <p>
                    <seg corresp="#KR2p0038_tls_001-13a.1" xml:lang="en">When the petty person precedes others </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0038_tls_001-13a.2" xml:lang="en">then he entangles them and go against them, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0038_tls_001-13a.3" xml:lang="en">[when he is behind others] </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0038_tls_001-13a.4" xml:lang="en">then he plunders them and destroys them, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0038_tls_001-13a.5" xml:lang="en">therefore it is said that </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0038_tls_001-13a.6" xml:lang="en">the petty person is easy to obtain </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0038_tls_001-13a.7" xml:lang="en">but difficult to employ, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0038_tls_001-13a.8" xml:lang="en">and in his deployment of the people </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0038_tls_001-13a.9" xml:lang="en">he necessarily requires perfection. </seg>
                </p>

            <p>
                    <seg corresp="#KR2p0038_tls_001-14a.1" xml:lang="en">I have heard it said: </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0038_tls_001-14a.2" xml:lang="en">“When (one's) conduct resides in [=depends on] oneself </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0038_tls_001-14a.3" xml:lang="en">and (one's) reputation resides in [=depends on] others, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0038_tls_001-14a.4" xml:lang="en">(one's) reputation is hard to dispute. </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0038_tls_001-14a.5" xml:lang="en">If one’s conduct is constant and untiring, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0038_tls_001-14a.6" xml:lang="en">one’s hold on goodness is relentless, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0038_tls_001-14a.7" xml:lang="en">even though the world does not know him, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0038_tls_001-14a.8" xml:lang="en">somebody necessarily will take notice of him, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0038_tls_001-14a.9" xml:lang="en">therefore the gentleman is forceful in his conduct, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0038_tls_001-14a.10" xml:lang="en">to attend to the attainment of fame. </seg>
                </p>

            <p>
                    <seg corresp="#KR2p0038_tls_001-15a.1" xml:lang="en">The gentleman listens to good words, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0038_tls_001-15a.2" xml:lang="en">to reforms his own words, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0038_tls_001-15a.3" xml:lang="en">he observes good conduct, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0038_tls_001-15a.4" xml:lang="en">to take it in himself, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0038_tls_001-15a.5" xml:lang="en">this can be called study. </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0038_tls_001-15a.6" xml:lang="en">I have heard it said: </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0038_tls_001-15a.7" xml:lang="en">“If it can be said </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0038_tls_001-15a.8" xml:lang="en">but it can’t be done, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0038_tls_001-15a.9" xml:lang="en">the gentleman does not say (it), </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0038_tls_001-15a.10" xml:lang="en">if it can be done </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0038_tls_001-15a.11" xml:lang="en">but it cannot be said, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0038_tls_001-15a.12" xml:lang="en">the gentleman does not do (it). </seg>
                </p>

            <p>
                    <seg corresp="#KR2p0038_tls_001-16a.1" xml:lang="en">[...] of the others is permissible (?). </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0038_tls_001-16a.2" xml:lang="en">I have heard it said: </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0038_tls_001-16a.3" xml:lang="en">“When one acts in the midst of danger </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0038_tls_001-16a.4" xml:lang="en">one (should) risks one’s life, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0038_tls_001-16a.5" xml:lang="en">when there is hunger and cold </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0038_tls_001-16a.6" xml:lang="en">there should not be meetings, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0038_tls_001-16a.7" xml:lang="en">in conducting affairs </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0038_tls_001-16a.8" xml:lang="en">there should be no litigations, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0038_tls_001-16a.9" xml:lang="en">a gentleman should not hurt others with rumors. </seg>
                </p>

         </div>
      </body>
   </text>
